COOKIE POLICY
This Cookie Policy applies to the Service of Nikkei Asia. Capitalized terms used but not defined in this policy have the meaning given to those terms in the Terms of Use.
The Website uses some third-party tools for purposes like monitoring Website performance, providing the Service and for the targeting, personalization and management of advertisements. Browsing the Website follows automatic access to such third-party servers, and each third party will obtain your access data etc. using cookies sent from each third-party server to your browser. The cookies will be saved on the User's hard disk or memory. If a User chooses to disable cookies, certain parts of the Service may not be available.
1. Opting out of cookies through your browser
Configuring cookie preferences
In some cases you may be able to refuse cookies by adjusting your browser settings. Refer to the "cookie" section within the "help" menu of the browser you use for further details.
2. List of information transmission to the third parties and opting out of third-party cookies
See the link below for information on how third-party services (which send your browser cookies) are used on our Website or Mobile App and how to opt out from their using your information.
Information Transmission
Nikkei may change this Cookie Policy at any time. Nikkei shall publish the revised Cookie Policy before it becomes effective, and will state its effective date.
